reviews.text:
Food was good, service was eh. 
Food took longer than we thought to get to us. Server was not very happy to be there.

It wasn't great but it wasn't bad. The food was good. I had a ham and cheese griller so you really can't mess that up. My mom had a club and my sister had a wrap. The wrap had honey mustard even though my sister said "no honey mustard". But I don't know if I can blame the cook or the waitress. 

Our waitress wasn't the greatest. She was a little slow and when we asked her what the soup of the day was she forgot to come back and tell us. When she did remember she couldn't remember what the soup was. Today it was cream or something, maybe crab or maybe corn and something vegetable. I'm not kidding that is what she said. Now as I am allergic to seafood they are very different soups! 

The prices there are pretty reasonable. For the three of us it was about 30 bucks. I will admit I have been there for breakfast and that was much better.

Took over 30 minutes to get our food. Soaked up two napkins worth of water from the egg white omelette and the "seasonal fruit" was some gray pineapple and another fruit I couldn't quite identify (maybe pear?) I sent it back, because I could make a more appetizing omelette at home and not have to spend $7.99. Chose not to try anything else from the menu after seeing their standard for a breakfast. Husband got eggs benedict which was fine, but nothing special. 


Overall, staff was very understanding and immediately took the omelette off of the check without question. 4 stars for the staff, but the food quality is just poor and we won't be back.

reviews.text:
Do a lot of take out from this place. Food is always fresh and the sauces are very good.
Freid rice, thai calamari are two favorites.

This place is our favorite place to order delivery and it's by far the best Chinese take out we have ever had.  The food is a little more expensive as compared to the average Chinese place but it's well worth it!  I highly recommend it!  Specifically, we love the crab rangoon, wonton soup, asian curry chicken and general tso.
Recently my wife and I got assorted veggie roll sampler and sweet potato roll!  Absolutely delicious!   Downside,  cheap on the Wasabi and ginger.   Like Arnold said, I'll be back.

reviews.text: Food was actually OK, but there is no heat here. Do not think you are going to eat in.

Please do not eat here!! Food is BLAH, service is terrible. This place has gone way downhill in the last few months. Not sure if new owners or new staff but yuck!! Panda and Bamboo Bistro will get my money from now on.

Consistently some of the best takeout Chinese food I've ever had. I was getting the lunch special almost weekly when it was colder. Huge portions, fantastic prices. Go to their direct website and order from them. Best scallion pancakes around. Their General Tso's is really good and all varieties of lo mein are great. Their dumplings and wontons are house made and taste it. The pork dumplings are fantastic, veggie dumplings have good flavor. Their boneless spareribs are fantastic. We havent had a bad meal yet. Delivery is super fast and their drivers are very nice.

reviews.text:
Really cheap? Pretty fast delivery? Open late? Yes to all three.

Is the food good? Not really. We were either outright unhappy (one dish went into the trash untouched) or just unimpressed with China Star. The fried rice was nothing special, and the egg drop soup was totally bland. Probably there are better Chinese takeout spots around here.
Food is low quality and bland. You order behind bullet proof glass and will never be greeted. Candy and cigs on display? Strange

This delivery/take-out only Chinese on Girard is great on price and presentation but the food is kind of meh.

Walking into this establishment makes one somewhat uneasy. Maybe it's the inch thick bullet proof glass, or the fact that you can buy cigarettes and Imodium, or maybe the two broke down chairs next to the ATM machine, maybe the sticky floors...not really sure if it's one of these things or a combination of all...I really felt like taking a hot shower though when I got home.

name: Mr Wish
description: Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Bubble Tea

reviews.text:
New location! Super convenient next to the Bambu. 

It's extremely busy- i waited THIRTY MINUTES FOR MY DRINKS!!!!!!!! I ordered 4 of the same drinks and it's ridiculous that I have to wait 30 minutes...????????????

Also, it is very unsanitary for long hair to be worn down while making bubble tea or any sort of food establishment. Please tie up your hair- I've seen you touch your hair with your hands and proceed to touch the drinks, i do not want to find hair in my drink.

I ended up going to the cashier and told her that it's been over 30 minutes for our drinks and they told me they ran out of milk tea..?? How are you going to run a bubble tea place and run out of milk tea? AND they ran out of bubbles. 

Highly disappointed in this establishment and location. Definitely will not be coming back for a while.

I would give negative stars if I could the workers personality are bad I asked if can add extra boba rudely said no extra allowed I also came three days in a row and first time they told me the waffle machine was broken second day they told me it was being cleaned and third day said oh it was not plugged in. And need to be plugged in and they they were busy so ...

Mr. Wish at Whitaker Avenue has such nice decorations and the workers are pretty nice. I bought five drinks on Tuesday, 11/5/19, and all the pearl milk tea tasted off. I thought it was just my drink but all my friends had weird drinks as well. I asked my other friends to try it and they said it wasn't just me and something was completely off. The boba in the pearl milk tea was not soft or even sweet, it tasted nothing like their signature tapioca. I contacted them through mrwishbencity about this. They opened my picture of the receipt and never replied. It's been four whole days and I'm really upset about this. Today, 11/9/19, I bought the tiger shark and it's nothing as advertised. My friend who works at the Chinatown Mr. Wish said this is nothing like the tiger shark. When she drank it, she said it tastes like regular milk and the boba is so hard. It's as if they didn't make the boba the way they were supposed to make it.

name: Panera Bread
description: American (New), Restaurants, Bakeries, Food, Sandwiches, Soup, Salad, Bagels, Breakfast & Brunch

reviews.text:
Ordered lunch from here. Delivery was really fast, so good work by the driver. 
Everything else was pretty lacking. Got my cookie order wrong (ordered choc. chip, got oatmeal raisin). 
The tortellini was dry and hard in places, indicative of sitting in a steamer tray for too long. Portions were really quite stingy for twenty bucks' worth of food. Everything was pretty bland considering how much salt is in it. 
It's a chain restaurant, so my expectations were set accordingly. Even then, I give it a "D".

Just wanted to say how much I appreciate the kindness that the manager Steven (?) showed me today 03/29/2020 during lunch time. I hurried in to grab lunch in between my shift at the hospital. And he was kind enough to put my meal on the house to thank the healthcare workers during this time with COVID. So thank you for making us feel appreciated when everyone else is quarantined at home. We essential workers are still front line trying to fight this.

This was the second time I have ever been here but I was running errands and wanted to grab a quick lunch. I never realized how big this location was! There is plenty of tables and booths more than any other location I have ever been to. They also have a kiosk ( which I totally missed walking in ) but you can skip the lines and order it all by yourself. I also liked how clean and how they were on top of cleaning/wiping down the tables. 

I ordered my go to pick two, I love that you can mix and create your own combo. As always it was delicious. Napa Almond Chicken Salad & the mac & cheese. I had always heard how good it was and wanted to try it for myself. The only problem is that its not diet friendly. I also liked they had 6 fresh brewed teas and lemonades. 

I will definitely make it a point to frequent this location more! 

Don't forget to sign up for their rewards program, after so many visits you can earn a free pastry or coffee or beverage.

reviews.text: This subway is very clean. They make sure that they keep all the food covered. The women makes the sandwiches very quick however the man, who happens to be new is not the quickest but he is getting better. I enjoy eating here because it is usually quiet.
I have been here a few times and while I haven't experienced an unhelpful staff, I have experienced a lack of condimints and ingredients. Avoid if possible
Terrible awful service here! Very rude staff the two times I have been here. Wanted to give it a second chance but clearly the employees are unhappy at their job.

name: Duck Donuts
description: Coffee & Tea, Donuts, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Food

reviews.text: Amazing made-to-order doughnuts!  They don't get much better than this!  Nice service and reasonable prices.

Was able to get here early in the morning Sunday for their grand opening weekend. I must say the lines may have been long but the doughnuts were well worth the wait. Considering the whole town seemed to have showed up for the grand opening I was not surprised to have to wait for an hour until I was able to get my made to order doughnuts. Luckily I was smart and ordered a coffee while I waited. 
The deal with this place if you have never been to a duck donuts is that every doughnut is customizable and made to order. So you can either choose a doughnut variety they make themselves or you can create your own. There were so many good choices and I decided to place my fate in the hands of the duck. I opted to get half a dozen and chose an assortment of donuts. My favorite easily being the maple bacon which literally tasted like a good morning breakfast. I would definitely make time to check this place out , especially if your a die hard doughnut fan like myself. You will be treated with one of the lightest but beautifully made fried circle of deliciousness.

Very impressed how fast the service was on such a busy weekend! As a big fan of Duck Donuts in NC, I was pleasantly surprised by the staff and enjoyed the mint chocolate donuts they suggested to me. I wish there was a little more seating to eat the donuts, however there may have not been much space since they just opened and had quite a crowd.

address: 202 Holland Rd, Ste 208, Wawa Shopping Ctr
description: Restaurants, Food Delivery Services, Food, Italian, Pizza

reviews.text: Won't be going back.  I orderer ONE cheesesteak and it was the worst cheesesteak I've ever had.  How can you mess up a cheesesteak?  There was very little meat on the roll.  The meat that was there was black from being on the grill for too long and the chesse - non exsistant.

Ordered delivery from Pizza Land and was pleasantly surprised. They have reasonably priced family specials. Food quality was great and the staff was super friendly. Pizza, mild and honey bbq wings and cheesesteak portions were huge and delicious. Will definitely order from them again.

TWO SLICE SPECIAL REVIEW ONLY

The price at $4.99 for two large slices of pizza and a soft drink was excellent.  The size of the slices was also more than expected. The service was friendly.  The room was small, with only two tables for those who want to eat their pizza just out of the oven when it is at its prime. So, this is basically a take out joint. 

We wanted a quick bite to tide us over until dinner. A slice apiece and sharing the drink was our intention. 

I requested that the reheat be "well done," in order to bring the ingredients back to life after sitting on display. 

What we received were slices that were not hot in the center where the cheese was thickest. That was likely due to the excessive amount of cheese piled onto the pie, out of proportion to the tomato sauce which seemed sparingly used. The result was pizza that could not be picked up by the crust because it was too heavy on the topside.  The taste was weak because of the cheese/sauce imbalance, and perhaps the quality of the cheese and sauce themselves.  The crust would have been improved with a little salt added to the dough.  

Not an impressive effort by Pizza Land.

reviews.text: When I order from them they always deliver pretty quickly and sometimes includes a free item. I've had their won ton soup, dumplings and a few of their platters by now and they don't disappoint. One time I tried to say what time I wanted them to come by and they arrived a half hour sooner but other than that always a good experience.

I used to get deliveries from this place, but saw info and pics online about the disgusting ways they prepare food outside behind the restaurant.  Vegetables on the ground thrown into a cooking pot for example...so filthy.  They need to be reported, better yet:  Shut 'em down!!
Have to get the lunch specials totally worth it. But its only 11-3pm. Hot and sour soup is awesome!

reviews.text: I've been so many Subways for lunch over the years, but this location is truly exceptional with keeping things fresh, delicious, and clean.  I go out of my way to go to this Subway.
my first time around 7:30 pm on a thursday. the service and food was excellent. just what i needed to fuel up and continue on my way. by the way the coffee was excellent too! thank you!
Clean facility, friendly staff, delicious food.  Staff really pile on the toppings and the produce are always fresh.  Highly recommend if you are interested in a (slightly) healthier option.

name: Kung Fu Tea
description: Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Bubble Tea, Coffee & Tea

reviews.text:
I've been on a mission to find the city's best Thai milk (bubble) tea. I noticed that the Kung Fu tea in South Philly has Thai milk tea on their menu, so I ordered one via the app.

I started drinking it in the car as soon as I picked up my order and realized that this does not taste like Thai milk tea at all. I am 100% sure this was just regular milk tea. I felt deceived. Aside from this, the order had the toppings, sugar and ice level that I requested. The bubble tea tasted like a standard milk tea, nothing to write home about. The boba was a tad sweeter than I would have liked. 

Overall, this was just a very unsatisfying trip and drink. Guess I will stick to Vivi for now.

I love Kung Fu tea and i am so happy that they opened one in south philly! i work near by and now i can get my drink all the time!

I got my drink during soft opening and the service was quick and the drink is good just like other stores.

The restaurant is very clean and decently big! There is adequate seating for all party sizes. The staff is attentive and helpful with your order. The bubble tea options are very large and very customizable. The tea itself is delicious and good quality. The most noteworthy thing about Kung Fu Tea is the bubbles. You can go to a million bubble tea locations as many times as you choose and consistently receive boba that is not quite right, or constantly different in quality. But this is not an issue at Kung Fu Tea. The bubbles are always perfectly made and consistently made. No matter when you go or how often you frequent the place, you can count on receiving perfectly cooked, delicious boba in your bubble tea. If chains turn you off to trying this bubble tea, I can assure you that quality is not affected by that factor. It is really worth a try!

reviews.text: Love their special order tofu. General tso or veggie tofu, they make it fresh to order. Takes about 5-10minutes. Also, their lo mein is some of my favorite in the area. Honestly, very good for a Chinese place in a mall. Yummmmm

stopped here for a quick lunch.  they have their own seating section which is nice so you don't have to fight for a table in the middle of the mall.  Had the sesame chicken with lo mein.  both pretty good.   also had an order of dumplings. they were pretty good too.  not as doughy as some chinese restaurants but better than most japanese restaurants i have had.  would eat here again if looking for a quick lunch in the mall.
Great place to grab quick bite. Make sure you try the egg rolls, not filling but very tasty.

reviews.text:
I was pleasantly surprised at the quality of food considering its a little stand located on the first floor of the plymouth meeting mall.  Due to the lack of traffic in this mall, you shouldn't have to wait long.  There is a wraparound bar (minus alcohol) for you to sit and eat.

Clean, fast, courteous. 

I tried the fruit smoothie assuming it was fresh fruit and ice..it is not! Still was ok..tried the green apple but not what I expected. 

They have numerous rolls,standard and special, and plenty of beverages to choose from including bubble tea 

The Philadelphia roll was fresh and so yummy,  looking forward to trying the miso soup
This is amazing food and it is very cheap! the chef makes amazing sushi and is very nice and considerate. Worth coming here again!!
I read great reviews here but honestly I was disappointed.  The roll with was so small it should have been called a mini roll.

reviews.text: Eat Lunch here occasionally and its very good. I get the 6 inch oven roasted chicken sandwich with bacon, cheddar cheese, lettuce, and bbq sauce every time and it is tasty. For a little extra you can make it a combo and add chips and a fountain drink. I like having lunch here because you don't leave with that glutenous feeling after having a sandwich unlike at some other places. Services is great and after coming here a few times one of the employees even remembered me and my co-workers orders.

Clean store with four or five places to sit and a television. Plenty of parking, but the lot has an unusual design with side spots across from slanted spots. Be mindful when pulling in and out of the place. Food is on par with other Subways. 3 stars, A-OK.

The only Subway on the main line! The staff is well informed, but they usually tend to be college students. They made me an awesome Autumn Turkey Sandwich that was topped off with their new cranberry sauce. The location can be crowded due to it's location, but the line moves quick. It has a small TV, but the staff always knows what to play. They recently added new sliding glass over the condiments so you can easily interact with staff.

reviews.text: Great boba! I always get their ear gray milk tea with less sugar. Boba is chewy and sweet! Their strawberry smoothie was not very good - not fresh, sugary and my kids didn't even drink it! But stick to their teas and it should be good!
Had their appetizers and found them uniquely packaged and delicious. I had the eel and the chicken teriyaki options. The Mango Green Iced Tea was delish. I'm coming back.

This is one of our favorite family treats! We are almost addicted. Our favorite is the matcha and chai flavor.  We are so excited that Doylestown finally has a place that carries boba.  They also offer a convenient Door Dash option, and this was very nice on a busy day at work. I highly recommend this place!

name: Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen
description: American (Traditional), Fast Food, Chicken Wings, Restaurants

reviews.text: Asked for the Spicy chicken sandwich, got the regular chicken sandwich. Fine. But the sandwich was hardly even warm. Cajun fries were room temp. I came in starving and left disappointed. The one in Eddystone is way better, everything there is hot and fresh.

Customer: "Can I get ranch sauce please"
Pop eyes: "Sauce are for tenders only" 
What!!?? I seriously don't know why some of the servers here are so CHEAP. Listen, I'm not asking for extra 10 packs, and I am willing to pay .50$ or 1$ ea. They get so annoyed when you ask for more sauce even if you are willing to pay.....crazy.

I've dined at several different Popeye's before and this one's among the nicer and cleaner ones. Only about 4 long tables, but it's never been busy enough when I've been there that I couldn't grab a table. Other ones make you pay for the sauces, but I forgot when I ordered and asked for some after and got them free. Self-serve drink dispensers, clean bathrooms. Waited about 10 mins for the noms, but at least it was a fresh batch (biscuits are #mmgood). My one complaint is that every time I've been here the sunlight shines bright through the windows with a glare that settles onto your face if you sit and eat as minorly inconvenient as that may be. Needless to say, I'll be returning whenever that irresistible Popeyes chicken calls my name once more. #cravingfood

name: BAMBU
description: Desserts, Bubble Tea, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Coffee & Tea, Restaurants, Vietnamese

reviews.text: This boba is super cool! They are creative in their recipes and menu items that go beyond just smoothies and milk tea drinks. They've ventured into drinks that are legitimately DESSERTS, obviously hence the name of this place. It's just sad that this place is so far away from where I live. :(
My family and I have never had this kind of drink before and it was really good! We loved the pandan and wish this was offered in NYC! Yum!

I have had friends raving about Bambu and had wanted to try it. Took the chance when I was able to visit Philly again. It was not as great as I expected, but it was not terrible either. This store was located somewhere I'd probably called like a mini-Viet area since everything was Viet. There was actually a moderate line when I got there and there's a lot on the menu. Of course, gotta try the che. It was okay. Unique. I enjoyed the pandan jelly and the coconut milk combo, but.. It was just not something I would want to go out of the way to return to. It was a good experience, but not something I'd go for compared to my love for other things. Definitely worth trying though cuz the pandan jelly is quite good.

reviews.text: This subway lacks customer service. I felt like the girl that waited on us was very rude and acted as if my daughter and I were inconveniencing her from talking to a male friend that was there keeping her company. I think I will just stick to getting my hoagies at WaWa.

I used to go to this Subway on an occasional basis to grab a quick bite for lunch or dinner.  Last November was the last time I will ever step foot back into this location.  I came in with 2 coupons.  Usually most places will run two separate charges so using 2 coupons isn't a big deal.  I ordered my sandwiches and went to checkout.  The owner refused to honor the second coupon and gave me an attitude.  Honestly, the customer service in this location sucks.  Owner also did not give me the corporate napkins too, which could possibly be a violation of their franchise agreement.  Corporate, please take note.

I came in to the Subway that I used to frequent for lunch on Tuesday, Aug 20, 12:38 pm. The restaurant was clean, and the food neatly on display appeared fresh. The store had just a couple of customers, and that was surprising being it was during the height of lunch hour. The gentleman behind the counter greeted me with, Hello, it's been a long time. He was the owner he had introduced himself years ago when I was a regular customer. I ordered my food a Spicy Italian on Herbs and Cheese roll and had requested my sauce be placed on the bread. There were some new toppings, so I was checking them out and not paying attention to the construction of my sub. The man asked sauce on top; I replied with "Did you put a good bit on the roll," I order it on the roll to help prevent it from dripping on my clothes. He made an angry face and proceeded to lift the contents off the roll and show me, I asked if there was a problem and he went on to reprimand me for having asked for a little on the bread, I may have used the word little but was only wanting to know if he put any on the bread because I wasn't paying attention and so that I knew there was sauce on it. There was no one in line behind me, yet so I was taken back by his giving me attitude. I took my sub to go, it was good but I have always been respectful to this guy and even tolerated his bad talking Subway corporation in the past because "they don't support the owners just have demands on them" I had given him frequent receipt reviews all positive and even did a yelp review years ago that was also very positive. A woman was at the register and was very kind, thanking me for coming in. When I exited the store, it was the last time I will ever go there. Maybe this explains how on a summer day during the lunch rush near a theme park, the store was not busy? After posting my briefly of displeasure with on the receipt survey I received an email from the owner, it was a boilerplate message saying he shared my feedback with his team to improve customer service. That was even more of an insult and showed how much he doesn't care about his customers. When I exited the store, it was the last time I would be there.​

reviews.text: Fantastic pizza and wings! The sauce they use is the best! Friendly staff! They go out of their way for ya! Fast delivery! Thanks Jocko's!!!!!

Oh man...this place is fantastic! My friend and I walk through the door and were greeted immediately and given front row seats at the counter.

They serve breakfast and lunch and have tons of combo platters and specials. Prices are also rather fantastic...I don't recall anyhing under 10 bucks but if it were, it's probably worth it.

I got the breakfast combo of crab cake, 2 eggs, homefries and toast- all for 7 bucks and it was over-the-top filling.

This place is smackdab in Norristown so perhaps if you have jury duty or just around town in need of a quick bite you should definitely stroll in.

The interior is small and the set up is cute- counter seating and several tables around. The owners are a lovely Korean couple who are friendly as heck and beyond accomodating.

I had an awesome dining experience here and if they started serving korean cusine, I'd be in there every day- I even told them so!

Have been going to this spot for months. Always was a great location for an affordable breakfast, decent food and friendly staff. Unfortunately, a recent change in wait staff was made which would cause us to look elsewhere now for breakfast. Experienced an unfriendly waitress who showed zero customer service abilities. We had about 5 things wrong with our order, some requiring food sent back and others requiring to just cancel items. And I hate sending food back! Needed to ask multiple times for the same thing before receiving it. I can take inaccuracies from a new employee who might be learning, but no tolerance for attitude. I suspect this waitress won't last long at all and would return with another staff change, as the food remains decent for the price. The owners seem nice and do there best to keep things flowing when busy. If ordering for pick up, I give it 5 stars.

reviews.text: This service at this subway is wonderful. The woman that works here is kind and goes out of her way to please the customer. It is subway so the sandwiches are the same but service is key. It is also the cleanest subway I have ever been in. As I was leaving the gentleman working was on his knees cleaning the legs of the table that people rest their feet on. They wipe down everything and are a great franchise representative of Subway corporation. If you are out shopping and want to grab an inexpensive bite to eat I highly recommend this location.
This is the best subway I've ever been to. The best food and so clean. I'll never eat at another subway!

Boyyy..let me tell you...still sitting in there as I write this review..the south-asian man serving me refused to remind me of what a BMT was? He said he didnt remember...then when i pressed a little more, he decided to get me out of his face quicker by telling me.
Never asked me if i wanted it toasted...but said "What else? (on the sandwich)" i had to ask that he not continue to veggies but toast.
Snatched my card etc.
Listen..rule of thumb...meanness is an illness, you should have called out of work.

3 stars because the lady who was there, i heard how she interacted with other customers and she was polite

reviews.text:
I had visited this place with my wife several years ago and was not impressed.  The local clipper magazine that just came had a front page advertisement that listed "Fresh Lobster", so I figured I'd give it another try as it's hard to mess up lobster and it's been nine months since our Lobsterfest in Maine.  I had a craving that needed to be satisfied!

Unfortunately King Buffet has not improved since our last visit.  The food quality was very hit or miss between selections, with the typical assortment of items that you can find at almost any Chinese buffet.  Freshness seemed to be an issue with some dishes.  Case in point: the melted butter for the crab legs was very stale and tasted like it was blended with cooking oil.  I couldn't use it.  

But most disappointing for me was that there was no lobster despite the recent advertisement.  The staff cheerily told me that the seafood company had no lobster, so sorry.  

When I was paying my bill, the friendly checkout girl told me that dinner prices are higher on the weekends due to additional menu selections.  When I inquired what the additional menu selections were she said "frog legs and mussels.  And sometimes we have lobster"  I can accept that a business may have supply issues that occasionally prevent the delivery of an item.  But to both advertise and charge for that item and not deliver will keep me from going back.

We went back on a weekend and the food was even better! They had a hibachi station which was great and they refilled the food faster. My only complaint was they were low on ice cream. But other than that it was super delish. Planning to go again soon.

Where do you start when talking about this place? I mean, obviously you can't hold high expectations for a buffet style restaurant, but even with low standards, this still falls below acceptable. The chicken was dried out like it had been sitting there all day, I watched them mix "fresh cooked" chicken into a container already holding the earlier stuff and just mixed it around. Definitely not healthy nor safe. Prices aren't bad, so if you want cheap food and cheap prices, go ahead, good luck though.

reviews.text:
Amazing place. I came here with a friend and had chicken Lo mein. It was delicious, fresh, and not super oily like some places. It had vegetables and the chicken was good. 

The prices are affordable , as well as their combos. It is a very clean place in and outside of the kitchen. The owner is so nice and friendly ! 

There are two tables so keep that in mind if you are coming to sit down & eat. There is also parking right in front of the restaurant or at the other businesses that are next to it. Recommend if you are near the area !
This place has really great food.  The General Tso's is delicious.  I order from here at least once a week and the food is very consistent. Delivery is also very quick.

Came here for a change. Last few times it was good and a nice change from all of the other Chinese restaurant in the area. This time though...blech. The pork fried dumplings were so fried they were basically burnt. The egg drop soup was a dark yellow color and had an odd lemony detergent taste, I didn't even finish that. And their chef special "lovers delight" which is supposed to be shredded beef and chicken with peppers mushrooms and other veggies and a special sauce, turned out to be old peppers a mushroom and a few pieces of shredded chicken and beef in a sauce that tastes like all the other sauces. Very disappointing probably will not be returning. They got one star because the egg roll was good.

reviews.text: Mediocre. Nothing special. Dumplings are very heavy, way too doughy. They got 2 stars because they were open til 10pm and the staff are nice.

Service is great- quality of food is horrible! We ordered some chicken wings which were $4.50- got 3 tiny drumsticks and 3 sad wingettes. Definitely not worth the cost! We also ordered 2 shrimp rolls- they were extremely hard on the outside and the insides were full of grease, I understand they were fried but they were oozing the grease they were fried in. The shrimp fried rice was tasteless. Over all spent $20 and wish I hadn't. Will not be ordering or taking out anything from this place. Such a shame because the staff was so pleasant.

This is the best Chinese restaurant around! We tried it tonight and had sweet and sour chicken, chicken with vegetables, boneless pork ribs, won ton soup and egg roll everything was amazing!! We will definitely be going back again soon!

name: Pho Saigon
description: Coffee & Tea, Beauty & Spas, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Shopping, Arts & Crafts, Costumes, Restaurants, Vietnamese, Food

reviews.text:
This has become my new Pho spot. After going to Pho Hoa for many years, my last experience there was just bad. I noticed a new staff, so I wonder if the ownership has changed. 

Regardless, a friend of ours recommended that we try this place out... and we were surprised about how fantastic this place is. The pho is delicious (just as good as the old Pho Hoa before it went down hill) and Pho Saigon is very new and clean. Sometimes, cleanliness can be an issue at Asian restaurants, so I am delighted that this place is kept very clean. 

My husband and I have been making a little trip out of it. We go to Pho Saigon for dinner and then drive over to the Monster Pets to look at puppies... He's some how able to drag me out of the store without buying a pup. 

Overall, I give this place 4 stars for the best Pho in Philly and for cleanliness. It's also located in a shopping center with free parking, so that's also a nice little perk as well.

you really can't go wrong with this place! I used to be a regular but started going to Nam Phuong more simply because my mom love their wraps. 
However, this place is definitely the place to come for authentic Pho.
Food was ready when I got there and still hot when I got home. It was very delicious, and the coconut drink is very refreshing!

reviews.text: This restaurant is not clean to a standard that is comfortable to me. Every once in awhile my kids ask to come here and this time was the worst yet. It is absolutely filthy in here. I would never serve food to my family from a space that looks like this.

Of the many Panera Breads I've been to (some even better in the area) this one ranks lowly on the scale of greatness.

All times that I have been to this Panera the staff are unfriendly, rude, act like they don't give a toss about customers or helping them, etc. Customers walk around blindly trying to figure out the most basic elements of a restaurant such as where to pick up your food from, or where to place an order to begin with. Asking the people at the register is useless as they always seem to find themselves too busy to assist customers who need help, and going to the other side where the kitchen is is also useless as these employees are too busy preparing food to provide any assistance to lost customers.

The food is less than average for a Panera Bread. As mentioned above the kitchen is hectic and probably a living hell given the way everyone steps over each other and tries to do their own thing without any kind of cohesion. The managers/supervisors look and sound mean, doesn't look like employees are working together so much as trying to survive the impossible traffic this location receives every day under the poor management.


All in all, skip this location. There are plenty of better eateries accessible around this Panera Bread. Don't give anymore of your hard earned money to this underperforming, poorly managed corporate chain that could easily be replaced with another.

Let me just say I LOVE Panera bread. This location though is absolutely horrible. I've ordered many times food from them. I ordered my lunch as usual, now it was delivered but it was missing the main part the SOUP. Which isn't a big deal i thought, well apparently after speaking with "Summer" was told that they do not deliver nor do they give refunds. I asked to speak to a manager AARON hoping i could actually get my lunch. Aaron was very rude and condescending. He did not apologize and tried to shift the blame on the delivery service door dash. I spend a lot of money eating there and this is the last time i will EVER support this location. After about 20 minutes of holding passing me back and forth btw summer and this manger Aaron They issued me a refund of 2 dollars for the missing soup. Disgraceful! They should have refunded the whole bill amount or try to fix the situation. Which they refused to deliver my soup, so i had to leave work and go get food some where else. So much for loyal customers, loyalty is not something Panera specializes in.  Very very disappointed

reviews.text: This place is a great spot for quick and cheap middle Eastern food...had the chicken rice platter, falafel, empanadas, gyro and samosas. Everything was flavorful and very reasonable in price. I also appreciate the promptness of delivery, my food showed up in no time! Gyro Express, you guys are awesome!!

So glad this place is in the neighborhood. Everything was AMAZING! The prices are reasonable. I ordered hummus and pita, samosa chaat, chicken maroosh, and chicken kofta kebab over rice. I LOVE Indian/Desi food, and was surprised when I saw a mix of the Middle Eastern and South Asian culture on the menu. Highly recommended! I will definitely order from here again.

Don't let the outside of this place deter you from trying their food. The inside is full of really sweet folks. They were patient when I felt indecisive. They gave me a sample of their chickpeas and it was delicious. I eventually went with the chicken and rice meal, a samosa, and my husband got a lamb kabob with salad and a side is tabouli salad. My meal was great. I loved everything about it and the portion size was enough for two so I definitely had leftovers. The samosa was flavorful. I wasn't crazy about the lamb but that's probably because I loved my chicken way more! The tabouli (got a small) was huge - a but dry but delicious when I mixed it in my rice. The service, food, and price point makes me really hope this place stays around

reviews.text: Could have been better. Unlike Chinese food at all. No taste soever. Seems like Depending on a persons personality, they serve the quantity and not evenly for everyone.

This place is amazing! I love the entire staff and I go there on a regular basis. I get one of three things, Szechuan tofu, spicy potatoes, or lo mein. The tofu is insanely good and I wish I knew how it was made!

For a mall food court vendor, I thought Master Wok was pretty good. They have a nice selection of dishes from which to choose. The only real problem I could see was the "spicy chicken" wasn't actually spicy at all. However, the other dishes we tried had enough flavor and the fried rice was good too. Service was pretty good too.

name: Kung Fu Tea
description: Taiwanese, Food, Bubble Tea, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea

reviews.text:
Recently went to Kung Fu tea.  Received $4 off couldn't use it and staff wasn't helpful at this location. Was charged 2X amount of $25 for rewards I didn't sign up for! 

The app needs to be clear with instructions and the store needs to hire staff who are helpful.  Spent $18 for 3 drinks which weren't good. 

I will not go to this Kung Fu tea at this location again !!!! 

Waiting notice from my bank to be refunded !!

Brand new bubble tea in the area, clean facility, and good service. Love the popcorn chicken and the honey milk tea; altho the sauce for the pop corn chicken was too little and the rice to avocado ratio for the avocado kani was very little avocado filling and a bit more on the rice side. It still taste good tho. Would definitely come back again.

I've been drinking KFT since I was a freshman in high school and when they only have one location at philadelphia chinatown. You can't go wrong with KFT as if it's one of the most famous franchises for bubble tea. Now it's closer to my house I am loving it even more

reviews.text: This Panera location is awful. They're always out of key ingredients, the staff is rude. Chips were sold out for over a month. I've never had a great experience here.

This Panera Bread is my go-to location for when I want to grab something to eat while working out of the office. I generally choose a seat in the back area, somewhat close to the bathrooms. 

It can be pretty cold in here, though, so wear layers if you get chilly easily and order a soup!

If in the mood for a pastry, definitely try the strawberries and cream scone. Oh heaven.

As we we're ordering the manager was taking inventory and everyone that walked through the door he scoffed at and said, "another rush before we close". It was 8pm on a Saturday night. His attitude was unwarranted for a place that deals with the public. The woman who took our order was over it, and was giving minimum effort. Worst customer service I have ever had at a Panera.

reviews.text:
Perfect spot for pho first timers. Nothing is going to wow you if you're very familiar with this cuisine. But for the first timer, this is a good representation of what pho should taste like. 

Get the well done steak if it's your first time. The more acclimated you get the braver you will become. The veggies are always bright and fresh (bean sprouts, Thai basil, lime wedges, slice jalapeño). 

This restaurant is a bit cleaner than those in the area. Good luck finding parking though if you're looking to make a weekend visit. The restaurant does have a lot of space so bring the family. 

Yes, there are better pho restaurants in the shopping complex. But if its your first time, then eat here. It will make a good first impression and you'll want to try pho again. 

I've got the formula...

It's your typical pho joint, not the best but good enough if you're craving something Viet. I haven't explored most of the pho options in the city, but compared to all of the pho I've had in my life, it wasn't anything special.

We ordered the banh uot cha lua with nem (folded rice noodles/crepes with Viet cold cuts), pho dac biet, and bun mam. Banh uot was solid, though to be fair, there's not much cooking involved. The pho was missing some depth to its flavor and the broth could have been a bit clearer. I was also disappointed that there wasn't any tripe in the pho either. The bun mam was flavorful but a bit greasy with a thick layer of oil on top.

Portions are good though and service is nice. Just remember to pay at the counter after you're finished with your meal.

So I bypass one of my usual favorites in the area to try this place... 
It's Thursday.... Evening.... 6pm. 
There's nobody in this restaurant. So I walk in anyway, and there I stood. Nobody came. So I seated myself. A woman appears with a menu and a glass of water... A hello would've been nice.. But I'm not here for pleasantries and casual chit chat... So I exhaled and looked over the menu.. 
Back comes the alleged hostess and asked me what I would like... Oh! You can speak... I was about to try out my broken sign language skills... If that didn't work, I would've channeled my inner 5 year old and simply pointed at the menu...
I give this woman my order, and this broad decides to interrogate me... "Have you ever had this before"?? As if I shouldn't order it if I had never had it before... This was the line of questioning I really needed the time I ordered a side of duck/goose feet inside Oregon Market because I saw everyone else ordering it. It had to be good, right?? It was f'n disgusting....
Where was I...? So I looked at her for about ten seconds and calmly repeated my order and off she goes... The optimist in me was hoping that the slick question she asked meant that I was in for an epic meal... It was aight. 
Check time... After winning roughly a trillion coins on a slots machine game on my phone, there still was no bill, although I could see the hostess sitting at the register, possibly playing the same exciting game that I was. The interest got the best of me. So I wandered over to the register to hopefully see what she was playing and pay for my meal. 
Long story short, the only parts of my meal that wasn't subpar was the bottled condiments and the glass of water.

reviews.text: This store is poorly managed. Not enough drivers. According to the online tracker, my order came out of the oven at 5:40 and didn't leave the store until 6:15. After waiting an additional 20 minutes, I called and canceled
Zero stars. Over an hour to prep one pizza and then had to call to cancel the order. Terrible.

This is the worst dominos in the world. They should get a prize for how awful everything is here.  

The pizza tracker said my pizza was finished at 5:40 and had already been inspected.  I called at 6:30 to ask where it was, and apparently the delivery driver was going to leave in another 10-15 minutes.  I guess he was just chilling while my pizza got cold.

Anyway, got the pizza a few minutes before 7pm, a full 2 hours after I had originally ordered. The pizza was cold, as were the lava cakes.  Not at all worth the money and I regret not ordering local.  Live and learn!  Don't give this place your business.

reviews.text: I needed/wanted soup today and options were scarce. I got wonton soup and chicken with broccoli. This is some of the best Chinese food around here. Great service, great prices and great food

Despite busy business, the manager/owner welcomed us with a bright smile...not always a typical gesture, sadly, offered by small town Chinese restaurants. As a vegetarian, I was very pleasantly surprised by a generous selection of vegetarian dishes. The one I ended up ordering was broccoli with mushrooms in yummy sauce. 
When I visited the restroom, I was again, pleasantly surprised by its cleanliness and fresh scent. For those of you who visit restrooms in a non-chain Chinese restaurant, you should know what I'm hinting at. 
All in all, if I live near the area, this would be my go to for a clean and friendly place to get my comfort foods.

So I was in the mood for some quick Chinese food. generalTsaus Shrimp. Hmmm- looked strange, never saw shrimp sticks. Was dry- tasteless- which leaves me to believe it was that fake seafood stuff.  Not what I paid for!!

reviews.text: They have really good Banh Mi! I've tried all their banh mi and my favorite is "Grilled pork banh mi". Highly recommend to have it as a go-to lunch :)

First time I went here I thought I'd never come back. But I did and I regret it. With so many options in Philly for Vietnamese fare, you need flair to stand out. This restaurant couldn't do that.

I don't have good memories of their pho...so I thought why not give it another shot. Maybe they've changed their recipes or made improvements since I last came. Nope. But I made sure to order a few items so that I'm not reflecting on that one dish that one time I came.

So here's what I got: their special pho dac biet, broken rice Combo, and rice with steamed chicken (Leg). A big reason why food declines in flavor is when shortcuts are taken to streamline. And I think that's what's the food tasted like.

The pho failed in many dimensions. The soup was just bone broth and lacked any type of other seasonings. The protein was chewy and bland. The pho noodles were overcooked. Cue the bad flashbacks.

The rice combo had mushy grilled pork (mushy, not tender), oversalted shredded pork (which was mostly pork skin), an overdone omelet...and their dipping sauce (nuoc cham) was very vinegary. 

Their steamed chicken dish (similar to Hainan chicken except eaten with a ginger dipping sauce instead of soy cause) is a specialty item that is supposed to make them stand out because it's not often found on menus at other Vietnamese restaurants. What I consider a successful dish is dependent on the tenderness of the chicken and the flavor of the dipping sauce. Sadly, Pho Ha Saigon did meet those conditions. Here's why their dish was so lackluster: the chicken was leathery meaning it was either overcooked or prepared ahead of time and their ginger sauce had texture and flavor issues (possibly due to using minced ginger instead of ginger julienne and their nuoc cham was not so good to start).

Given that there are better options, I sadly won't be visiting again.

Here's my update on why I dropped a star. The food was the same. I got pho while my brother got com suon nuong. But the problem was the serving time. There's no reason why his dish should be served when I'm almost done finishing up my bowl. That's a good 20 some minute difference. Tables around were getting their food just fine but we had to remind the waiters two times that my brother didn't get his plate yet. 

So yes. A star was dropped due to the service.

name: Subway
address: 501 S Broad St, Ste 13, The Pavillion

reviews.text: The worst Subway I have ever been to in my life. The person who was working there threw the sandwich together with no care at all. Then the taste was so garbage. Ruined my day.

I can't really rate anything besides false hours. I showed up on Saturday night around 840 and the doors were locked. The signs clearly said open but the crew could be seen cleaning up for the night. What are the hours of operations? Even on yelp it has you open til 9pm... Your lose was someone elses gain. The pizza steak at Palermos across the parking lot was amazing.

I purchased a very simple ham and cheese sandwich for my kids.  There was a line of workers to keep things moving along somewhere along that line my sandwich was switched with the person next to me.  When I got home my kids sandwich was the totally wrong sandwich.  When I returned to the subway to get a correct order, and asked if they were going to compensate me for the 45 minutes of lost time they simply shook their head no and said they would make me the right sandwich.  Totally unprofessional !!!  People, and this means the owners of this place, should be responsible for their business and the mistakes they make or get out of business.

reviews.text: One of the best Subways I've been to. The people are always nice and the sandwiches are always perfect. They also have a lounge area with seating and a big TV.

I stopped into this subway for lunch.  Wow!  It was great.  Excellent food and service.  They have a small lounge with a large tv.  Bathroom was spotless and welcoming.  I got two free cookies - probably because I brought my whole family - all 7 of us.  Cost over $60 but worth every penny. We had a really great lunch and enjoyed watching the eagles game at the same time.  Will definitely come back.  Great owner - friendly and knows sports pretty good, but not great.Gary really is terrific.

This Subway is great. The owner Gary is warm and this Subway tastes good. Love the chicken sub there. It is also really clean there and if you need to pick up a few other items there is a convenience store in there as well!

reviews.text: First things first; I should have known better than to order a lobster roll from Panera. That was just dumb on my part. If you're thinking about it, don't order it. I felt like I was eating chewy imitation crab. Not buttery at all like it's supposed to be, and the roll was sub par. Soft is one thing, but soggy is a total turn off. My sister's avocado chicken bacon sandwich was supposed to be toasted. It was on yet again another soft piece of white bread. Can't go wrong with the bacon cheddar soup. That's about the only good thing I got out of this location, and the only reason this review got a second star out of me.

I pre-ordered my meal on-line.  I arrived into the store at the  time stated when I placed the order.  It was not quite ready yet.  After waiting another 10 minutes I asked how much longer.  The girl at the front who was on her cell phone said they haven't even started it yet.  I told them to just cancel the order.  It is completely ridiculous that  I had to waste my whole lunch break when the order should have been ready close to the time promised.  I will NOT be back to this Panera.

I was at this location a few weeks ago prior to starting class.  Staff was friendly and offered soup and sandwich suggestions...  Zaria was the counter person and she was great!..  Great place to go in between classes...

Such a waste of $38.

they aren't trying to be ruth's chris. perfect little stop for a slice and soda. super clean, pleasant atmosphere and great staff. glad i stopped, hadn't planned on it. if i find myself nearby again, would absolutely return.
The info here is inaccurate, it is open until 5 am, and that is what earns it 5 stars first. Also they are willing to make changes to items on the menu. Super helpful and friendly even at 1 am.

reviews.text: Beware they sell dead clams !!! I got clams with tamarind sauce to go and when I get home this is what I saw, all the clams are not open cause they're dead. They can't not charging people $20 for dead clams !!! I will not come here again

The place is great! I'm excited that we finally have bò né in Philly. The meat is slightly over cooked, compared to what I had in Vietnam but it still taste good. It comes with xiu mai and salad. Banh mi is additional charge though. My mom got bánh cun and she said it was good too. My mom is pretty picky with Viet food and this is her second time here. Overall I'm definitely recommend this place. I'm not sure why they're not getting more stars.

My sister and I came in here for breakfast. Per the other reviews, we saw that they had different menus for the difference times of the day so we were looking forward to that. 

Upon walking in, we were seated right away. When the waiter brought us our waters, there was a fly in my sisters cup. Gross! 

We ordered our food - Bo ne dac biet and the canh bun and bread. The canh bun's broth wasn't hot enough. It came out Luke warm and the soup was very sweet. The bo ne came with xui mai and that was very sweet too. The meat was tough, gritty and overly marinated. The warm pate was the best part of the meal and everything else was either warm, soggy, or too sweet.

reviews.text: Yummy subs! This place has a great selection and friendly staff. The meats are delicious and the portions satisfying.

I'm a big fan of Jersey Mike's Subs and wish I had known about them long ago. However, after a show at the People's Light and Theatre In Malvern, I came across this Jersey Mike's on the ride home. 

I walked in and was greeted by the sight of a large restaurant filled with tables, beach pictures on the walls and two TVs. 

I decided to get the Jersey Mike's Combo meal, which came with a sandwich, chips and a fountain drink. I ended up getting the Famous Roast Beef and Provolone on the Parmesan bread. The sandwich was made perfectly. The roast beef was juicy, but thinly cut while the provolone cheese had a nice, mild taste and was very fresh. I also got some tomatoes and oregano on top, which brought the whole sandwich together. I also loved the flavorful of the hearty Parmesan bread. 

They also had a great array of lays chips, which came the with the combo meal. I ended up getting the baked Lay's barbecue chips.

Also, the staff here was very nice and friendly. I especially liked how they gave me time to order, cut the roast beef perfectly and recommended the combo meal to me. They also were great in putting together the perfect ratio of toppings. The prices here were not too bad either. Unfortunately, they forgot to give me a cup for my fountain drink, which was part of my combo meal.

Altogether, this Jersey Mike's Subs serves great food with friendly staff!

Maleek, the manager, is great.  I ordered 10 subs to go, for my wife and grandkids.   Absolutely superb.  I was a hero with the grandkids.  They just loved the subs.  I bought a wide variety so everyone had a choice.   Got some great sides too.

reviews.text: This place was SO dirty and the cheesesteaks my fiancé and I got were bland and raw. The employees were incompetent. Will never be visiting this Jersey Mike's again.

Same fresh food and nice staff as one of their other stores not quite as fast as the other store I visited but place was immaculate and conveniently located next to Starbucks. 
We love the oil vinegar mixture on the Italian.
They were running some special on subs since they just opened and we were happy to find out we got our meals for like 2 bucks!!!! 
It does appear someone here is community minded as they according to my information work with MS of Delaware I believe .. 
That's nice to see and made me a loyal customer. You guys are the best thanks a lot!!!!

My fiancé and I have ordered from other jersey mike locations in the past, and have never had a problem. However today we ordered via DoorDash (3 rd party ordering site) and when our order arrived only 1/4 of our order had arrived. When we called the store to ask if we could get a refund, they instructed us to call back later as they're too busy to issue a refund. We went to the store to pick up the rest of our order. When speaking to the manager on duty, he said "that's what happens when you order with DoorDash." I understand that it's lunch time, and they were busy, however customer service could've been better.

reviews.text: Great sushi but can get the same in Chestnut Hill. I asked for all you can eat for the advertised amount of 25.00 but when I got the bill they added an 11 dollar charge for the kids special which was never ordered and then an additional $5.00 just to bring the leftovers home. I already paid for the food. Walked out with my seltzer and a zero tip. Disgusted by the extra charges.
Good food, well prepared. And great prices for rolls! Very small place, so be prepared to wait during rush times. Have had many good meals here - both eat-in and take-out.

The sushi is insanely cheap but it does come with a trade off with quality. I do come here often because it's close. A lot of the rolls are fried but honestly i don't know if I would trust the sashimi here. It's not terrible, but not impressive either.

reviews.text: Placed an order at 438pm through grubhub. I still didn't recieve my order at 615pm, but I figured its busy and Friday. I called and they told me it was about to head out. 7pm rolls around and I call again. They told me they didnt recieve my order... now why couldnt they figure that out when I called at 615?  I just cancelled the order and sent my business elsewhere. Needless to say I will not be ordering from them again.

I saw two flies flying around the counter of slice ordered pies. The blonde girl stood as I was deciding on what, hours old, slice I wanted to order. We watched as two flies landed on the pies. Making eye contact.... She never even shoo'ed the flies away. Where there are multiple flies.... There are surely little white creepy crawlers. Especially if the staff doesn't consider them disgusting and something someone wouldn't want landing and obviously hanging out on what they're about to eat. This place is run by people who are too busy flirting with each other or catering to Bensalem police department who leave their cars idle for an hour, to have time for customers. I looked directly at her and said 'maybe I won't have pizza, thanks though' she couldn't have cared less and turned around to rejoin her conversation. I did her a favor. I thought id do her a favor and write this review. You're very welcome.

Ordered for the first time on Friday Night! Food was delivered to our Friends house. We were having a Fantasy Football draft. We ordered a pizza a few Sicilian pizza's. Wings, cheeses steaks and fries! Everything was delicious and on point! We will definitely order from here again when we head back home to the Northeast!

reviews.text: This is the best Chinese restaurant to go to in Norristown. Their chicken is always moist, their rice is always fresh and good! When I call to order, I get treated nicely, and they never get my order wrong. This is the only place I'll ever buy from in Norristown. I tried the other Chinese food places, and they've never been as good as Golden Key.

This used to be my favorite Chinese store around. I lived in the area since 2008 and I would eat from here all the time if I didn't feel like driving to Norristown for a lot more food for a better price. I didn't mind paying more. This store have went down hill a little since owners changed. I think a new cook have came into play over the past year. The food is just not the same anymore. I was not happy the last 3 times I came here and I switched to something new. But now I am completely done. The shrimp and broccoli used to be very good with nice size shrimp. The broccoli is on the hard side and the shrimp is slimy. Yuck. After ordering this two different times, I gave up. Shrimp egg foo young always been the best here. Now the egg is mushy and soft. Major turn off. They do have the best beef on a stick but for $6 plus tax, I think the beef should be almost the size of the stick it's on like most Chinese stores. Its about 2-3 inches long. Rip off. The chicken on the stick was so over cook and dried out. You can't enjoy them. Shrimp Lo mein is still do-able but its not as juicy and tasteful as it used to be. After 3 disappointment visits, I have waited awhile and said I can settle for some shrimp fried rice. You really can't go wrong there. Well I was incorrect. This has been the worst and normally my daughter orders this with everytime and it's always good. This rice was hard, a major turn off. It was so light as if they tried to fry white rice and serve it. It was so not good. Sad to lose a loyal customer who orders from here at least 2x a week.

Golden Key is the best Chinese restaurant in the area. I drive best multiple Chinese restaurants just to eat here. They have good customer service, and have your food ready quickly and correctly. 
The food is seasoned and flavorful. The meat dishes are hearty and has a nice bite of meat without tons of breading. The dishes such as the general tso's chicken, etc is cooked very well with a nice crisp to it without over doing it. 
They deliver within a wide distance and are very quick with their deliveries. They are a nice, clean establishment. I would recommend this Chinese restaurant to anyone looking for some delicious Chinese takeout in the area.

reviews.text: My husband and I take turns stopping in on the weekends for their egg flatbreads. They guy who works in the morning on the weekend is great -- friendly, efficient, and remembered us and our orders after a couple visits.
They are skimpy on sandwich toppings.  I had to ask numerous times and then the sandwich maker would put a small pinch on.  If you want a sandwich made how you like it dont go here.

This location is probably one of the worst subways I've ever been in.  

The guy behind the counter barely looked at me while I ordered, asked me to repeat things several times, and just seemed to not care at all that he was at work.  They were out of sprite zero, doritos, and teriyaki chicken.  

I could have handled all of those issues if the sandwich was at least on par with other subways, but it wasn't.  The bread was stale and crunchy, despite seeming fresh and pulled from the oven, and the onions were slimy and on the verge of not being safe to eat.  

There's another subway 2 blocks away on Chestnut.  Go there instead.

reviews.text:
I just returned from this store and here is my experiece. 1) The chicken is not fresh and I could not eat a 6" sub and had to throw it away. 2) Noticed that they put lot lettuce but very less of other items 3) The meat in the containers look dried as if they put that 2 days back. 

Not worthy to go.
Don't usually leave reviews but this subway changed that! The subway was nice and clean looked like a subway from 2050 or something...workers were on top of keeping everything clean and neat. 10/10

Terrible experience... the cashier lady's attitude was super rude ... upon asking price for the drink or chips she stares and says take anything everything is free here .... coupons sent by subway have many restrictions here ... they make up their rules 
... definitely not going here again. 
Need to work on good communication with the customers ... we don't work here so we don't know pricing and coupons sent by subway need to have mentions as to what is included ...

name: Subway
description: Fast Food, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Salad, American (Traditional)

reviews.text: I was there today at 1130am getting some food. Ordered a sub and the guy doesn't ask if I wanted it toasted even though I did. Then one of the wall menus fell to the ground which is a representation of this subway location..anyways, he then picks up the sign with his gloves and then proceeds to start handling my sub and puts my toppings on my sub.  Like come on, you kidding me. I wish I was a food inspector so I could fire him right then and there.  I asked him to change the gloves and he said no no it's fine.  I said dude, no I dont want to get sick from that. He made me another sub like a little beep and wasn't very nice about it.  Wont be going there ever again.  Wasting my hard earned money for that bs..forget that.

Worse Subway in America . I walked in the employee was on his cell phone . I ordered a soup and sandwich. The guy put his phone down and grabbed the bread . No gloves , didn't wash his hands or anything .When I told him I'll just take the soup instead he proceeded to the refrigerator and pulled out a cold bucket of soup telling me he just has to warm it up. When I asked to cancel my order he became very disrespectfully.
Went to Subway to order a sandwich and they're closed before 10pm. The restaurant was clean as if they closed hours ago. I'm calling corporate in the morning.

name: Red Mango
description: Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt

reviews.text:
PROS: Fresh toppings, clean space
CONS: Runny yogurt (faulty temperature or quality control)

I'm an avid fan of froyo. I'm also a fan of the Red Mango in ATX. This particular Red Mango fell short of my expectations by a bit. The yogurt (which I expected to have a decently thick, creamy consistency) was runny.  The flavor was still good though!

Philly is home to many frozen yogurt shops including Sweet Ending and Yogorino. Red Mango certainly gets the job done as well.

They have more than a few self-serve ptions - with the majority being fruit-flavored, including White Peach and Mandarin Orange.

As with most froyo joints, you've got a wide variety of fruit, candy, and chocolate toppings. 

Red Mango Frozen Yogurt ($0.49/oz)

The GF opted for the classic with a medley of fruit and granola. The yogurt was tart and the fruit was ripe - nothing wrong here!

Red Mango will get the job done if you're craving some froyo. Still, Philly has plenty of froyo joints and I don't really see how Red Mango separates itself from the rest of the crowd.

I love Red Mango, and I was surprised that it took them (or any of the other major froyo chains) so long to move into CC Philly. This is the first self-serve Red Mango that I've been to, and given that it was one of our first warm weekends it was not as crowded as I anticipated - but it does not bode well for when the heat reaches its peak in summer. The layout is fine, with the 10 different rotating flavors on the back wall, leading to the toppings bar that has a large and nice assortment of fruits, nuts, cereals, etc. There are tables and chairs too for patrons, and a restroom in back behind the froyo. The froyo flavors are tasty, but most importantly for froyo the TEXTURE is smooth and creamy, and relatively satisfying for froyo. WAAAAAAYYYYYY better than Sweet Endings.

BUT the moment there is a crowd of people trying to get froyo, the entire interior will instantly be clogged as patrons try to taste different flavors, can't make up their mind, wait in what will definitely be a slow line to get toppings, and THEN pay at the cramped register area...it'll be a shit show with half melted froyo by the time you pay and can *technically* eat your creation. We'll see what things look like in a month or two, once it's late spring and schools are out...

reviews.text: Just wanted to add that the very nice owner did contact me to offer a free replacement baguette! And although I wasn't able to make it to the market last weekend, I will do so soon. I really appreciate the excellent customer service. They obviously care alot about their product and their customer's experience!

We bought a loaf of sliced Honey Wheat Sandwich bread at the Collingswood Farmers Market in NJ & really liked it. I look forward to seeing them again so I can try other things. The vendor/owner (?) was so nice & chatty. Definitely will buy from them again.

Tried a slice of the vegan apple bread today and tried to save the other half of the gigantic piece for later... but I couldn't! Not too sweet, super hearty and tasty, with just enough cinnamon in it to tie it all together. Usually vegan sweets try to compensate with a lot of oil and sugar, but I felt pretty good about eating this, as it tasted fresh and had a good balance in the flavor.

Sandwiches aren't terrible -- that's not a great way to start a review LOL!

However, they don't put much care into making your sandwich, they skimp on the meat/toppings, and it seems like they are just trying to get you out the door as fast as possible, instead of making sure you have a great sandwich and pleasant experience. 
I appreciated that they used gloves when making my sub.

reviews.text: I used to love this place as a kid, about 25 years ago. I decided to go back a few years ago and see how it held up. They still serve solid pizza and cheesesteaks all these years later. I went back again today for a good (cheese) pizza and some tasty fried ravioli. Great option for a local pizza place you can rely on for good food.

This used to be a family favorite, as we have lived local for 30 years! Over the past few months, the food and the service has been less than satisfying.

The pizza lately has little-to-no flavor and is COVERED in way too much tasteless sauce, so much that the cheese can't even stay on and is usually all over the box when it's delivered! The fries are always soggy and never taste like they were cooked long enough, but most recently we ordered cheesesteaks and the rolls were stale and hard as bricks!!

It's disappointing with a family of 5 and spending $50 each time. And then the customer service has also gone down hill! When I call for an order they always make it seem like you are bothering them by calling, and speak incredibly unprofessionally using phrases like "uh huh" "yup" and "what else." 

One time my mom ordered and forgot to give the credit card number over the phone. I called back and the lady actually SIGHED at me. For calling to PAY!! Then there is a creepy older driver who always asks me about my toddler son which makes me uncomfortable. Sadly, this place is no longer a 'family favorite'

Positives - In my opinion, they've got really good pizza. No, nothing is mind blowing, but more than solid and nothing to complain about. Granted I don't come here very often, but I've never experienced anything subpar or awful.

The Buffalo tails are off the hook. Great buffalo sauce that's slightly sweet, but balanced out by a little heat.

Negatives - Again, I don't come here often, but I've never had anything bad. The pizza fries weren't very good and lacked sauce and cheese, but it wasn't a deal breaker.

The customer service was fine to me, but I could see how they could possibly rub some people the wrong way.

reviews.text:
Moving to southern Chester Counity from NY it is very hard to find decent Chinese food, this unassuming little place outide of the Kennet Square Borough was a pleasant surprise the food was fresh and tasty (not dried out and overcooked) the deserts were not great but the quality of the food and staff made up for it.
skip the Chinese food in Giant Food in Jennersville and forget the two take out places in Oxford  That are practically next to each other very odd!
make the trip to this little buffet in Kennet Square you won't be disappointed

Do not eat here unless you have an appreciation for toilet time! A lot of toilet time. This is the second time I eat here and both my father and I got very sick. I would recommend spending a little more money and going to Lily's asian cuisine in town instead!
I've been in here a few more times since the first visit and have come to appreciate their food more. Egg drop won ton soup is very good and entree vegetables are not overly done.

reviews.text:
This Subway location is relatively new, and although technically located on Market Street, the entrance is actually on 4th, right next to the rear entrance of The Bourse.

This location has ample seating (a bonus for any Old City lunch spot), and I've never been unable to get a seat, even during the lunch rush. The lines are managed efficiently, and I've never had to wait too long for my order. They definitely run a pretty tight ship here. 

The one and only complaint I have is that kids from the charter school across the street have taken to hanging out in there sometimes. The managers do their best to kick the kids out, but I've been in there more than once when their rowdiness was an issue.
My bread was so stale it broke n flaked off as I picked my sandwich up. I couldn't even eat my sandwich because the bread was so bad

Thankfully last Friday all of the issues I bitched about in March were more or less corrected.

The store was very clean and the staff was actually cleaning the entire time we were there.  Partially that was accomplished because even though it was during what I would have assumed would have been a busy lunch rush, the place was deserted.  Over the course of twenty minutes every table got wiped, the soda fountain nozzles all were taken off & cleaned and all trash was taken out. #impressive

The food itself was typical Subway dreck where even when it's right it's still only right to a point as the bread was too soft almost like it was underdone and the apples in the cooler were mostly brown but whatever.

For better or worse it's cheap, it's filling and the location is perfect for when we're in town.

reviews.text: One of my go to lunch places at work, I've had many dishes from here some good..some OK. The lady that works there Rebecca is pretty cool an down to earth. My favorite dishes are the Thai fish and the udon noodles with shrimp. Only thing they charge extra for onions but it shld come with the meals!
Food is very bland, the guy who works there is kinda rude. Don't waste your time like I did 2x!

Even though I am Chinese and I eat Chinese food alomost everyday, I still like this place. I like rice noodles most, orient express had the tastiest Singapore rice noodles I have, the taste of curry is not strong. There are chicken, pork abd shrimp but I just like shrimps. The other item I ordered was the shrimp udon, I just dont like the brocolli, and I like it spicy. 

Just sometimes you have to wait a little longer for them to make the food.

reviews.text:
I am pro-immigration and pro-service worker, but had serious problems with language + communication at this subway. Like, if I can tell someone is making a genuine effort to communicate, benefit of the doubt, immediately.

BUT...at this subway, there was some kind of massive problem with speaking and eliciting a response that coincided with the original request. very confusing. there was also a problem with determining whether the sandwich makers really cared if he heard you or not????

that sandwich was fine though???? it just took a long time to achieve. 

very weird subway.
When I want Subway, this is my go-to location. The sandwich artists are always pleasant and I love that the quality is consistent each time I visit.
Decent place...except for the annoying droning pop music they have on, I think it's that local 102 station.

reviews.text:
This football season has been nice for me. The Eagles have been doing well. Knocking on wood, my fantasy teams have been also doing well. I also discovered China One as I looked for the Chinese restaurant that opened the earliest on a Sunday right before spending an afternoon *gasp* away from watching football. 

Since then, China One has been my go to spot before those 1:00 games. An odd choice, but it hits the spot to keep me from getting myself sick by overeating pizza and wings. The Eagles also are 3-0 on days where I ate at China One!

The Wonton soup is the best around. The pint is only $1.85, and it has 4-5 MASSIVE and delicious dumpings swimming inside.  I go the literal extra mile to order here rather than China Express because of this. The order is always done within 10 minutes, the staff is friendly, and the price is right.

They delivered me food when I called 10 minutes prior to then closing! The food was one of the bests that I have had, too. I will definitely be ordering again, just at an earlier time for sure! Thank you China One!

The food was good. The portions were HUGE!
This is basically a good take-out place.

Had a problem with the physical appearance inside.
Everything needed a good scrubbing.
Tables,chairs,napkin holders,counters--all were sticky and dirty.

Glad I took the food home to eat!

reviews.text: Everything here is really good. It's easy to look over but I highly recommend coming here if you're in new town
ALWAYS amazing food. perfect place for a vegetarian, love it! i usually get the vegan cheesesteak but today i got the vegan crabcakes, and they were fantastic! this place never disappoints.

I guess everyone is entitaled to there own opinion. While the food was very good, the atmonphere is horrible. It is dark and dingy with no windows. it is basically a basement. Our service was horribe, The tables are tiny and she failed to remove our dishes so many times there was no rood for our food. We also were not served bread as I noticed every table had bread but us--I had to ask for it. I would not return even though the food was good.
