name: Panera Bread
description: Sandwiches, Restaurants, Soup, Breakfast & Brunch, Bagels, Food, Salad, Bakeries, American (New)

reviews.text: i like getting the soups and sandwiches at panera bread, but its a hit or miss here. depending on who makes the food, sometimes it turns out delicious, some days the sandwiches are extra dry and lack flavor. they need to get it together

By all means, if you value your health, do not eat from here. I recently ate at Panera in Jenkintown and had the worst experience ever. First, I placed a mobile app order and decided to pick it up around 12 for lunch. When I got there, my order wasn't in the "Online Orders" section of the store. I asked the cashier girl if she could locate my food and it was sitting on the counter behind her. She looked at the receipt for a few minutes, looked around like she needed help with something, then finally handed it to me. I'm not sure why it was back there or why she was acting so strange around my food since it was paid for and sitting there for pick-up. Next, I get home and open up my package with my chicken quinoa broth bowl with French bread and the bread isn't in a cover or wrapped up, it's just lying on top of the plastic bowls. I eat the sub par food, which tasted strange, and went on with my day. I didn't eat dinner that night since I wasn't feeling too well. I woke up the next morning with serious stomach cramps and nausea. I realized about 2 days after I had eaten the food that the Panera is what got me sick. I wasn't able to eat solid foods from Thursday - Tuesday. I called corporate (who were very helpful) and explained to them what happened. Since this Panera is not corporate owned, they contacted the store manager and she gave me a call. Jennifer, the store manager, was extremely rude and insensitive. She stated that none of the food is made at the store. Instead everything comes prepackaged and they just microwave it and serve it. That's just gross to start off with. I thought this food was fresh, not frozen, packaged and shipped in order to be reheated and served. I might as well eat leftovers. The quality of this food is not worth the money spent on it. Next, she said that there is no way I could have contracted anything from her store because nothing is cooked on premises. But isn't the food handled when reheated? Or the server doesn't wash his/her hands? Or when it gets put into the container? Or how about when the bread is just laying on top of plastic that hasn't been washed or cleaned? Then she stated that I must have "gotten the flu from somewhere else." I didn't know that Jennifer is also a Doctor/Panera Bread Manager. She assumed I didn't get sick from there, she didn't say sorry, she didn't help in anyway possible. I didn't want any compensation or gift card or  anything; I just wanted to let someone know that something in their food made me sick. After this unbelievable conversation with her, where she badgered me and made me feel worse about my situation, I called corporate back and they contacted the district manager. He spoke to me and said he would talk to her and the staff about customer service. Honestly, she needs to learn about customer service, being friendly, and understanding the situation before letting ignorance and stupidity get in the way of clear judgement. Hopefully Jennifer gets the proper help she most desperately needs. If I were you, I wouldn't risk eat at this Panera or any Panera for that matter. It's just not worth it.

I came here for lunch with my date and ordered the turkey cranberry flatbread and 1/2 Fuji Apple chicken salad. I thought both were amazing; however I did switch out the Fuji dressing for their vinegarette.

We didn't have any problems with the service and our food was made promptly even though there was a lunch rush. Everyone is right about cell reception; it's awful. If you're planning on getting some work done, I'd find another place! Other than that, everything was good.

reviews.text: Went around 7am to this location to get a bagel was not crowded at all. There was a customer waiting for his order a dozen of bagels I believe. I counted 4 employees working only one cashier though she was picking the bagels and cutting them. the other workers were in back area I saw the manager and made eye contact with her a couple times hoping she would wait on but she was busy talking to another girl. I waited about 5 minutes to finally place my order. After you order you have to go to back to get order which I will say this was rather quick. I asked for a toasted bagel with cream cheese bagel was barely toasted cream cheese was in a small container which was a brand I never heard of was horrible. I usually go to Manhattan bagel a couple stores up but was very crowded. Thought I could save time and go to panera but probably spent same amount of time for a far inferior product.

Beware of online ordering! Just got back to the office, only to find my chicken Caesar salad has no chicken in it. I requested avocado, which they did put in, but they put in two small pieces. What a ripoff.
Friendly staff, quick efficient service, and located conveniently in an awesome shopping center. I think this Panera is a great option to stop for lunch if you're out and about running errands.

description: Fast Food, American (Traditional), Food, Chicken Shop, Chicken Wings, Desserts, Restaurants

reviews.text: We ordered takeout and when we got home, one of the fries and sandwiches we ordered were not in the bag. My wife tried to call the location and the phone rang endlessly. She tried a few times. Then she gave up and went online and filled out an online complaint form and received a canned response back saying "sorry, we'll try to do better next time." Well, there won't be a next time for us.

My only complaint about this store and most other Popeyes in the surrounding area is that they never have tenders fresh. They always make you wait at least  5 minutes for fresh ones. I guess it better than getting nasty dry chicken lol. I make sure that I never get food from here unless I have the time to wait.

My better half was craving southern-style chicken tenders and biscuits. Reviews for this Popeyes location were good so took a detour on the way home to pick up the food order.

Prior reviews mentioned that this was a clean location and this is very apparent when one steps into this joint. The interiors are super clean and well maintained (including the rest rooms). 

The chicken tenders were freshly prepared and the last time we had memorably good ones from a fast food spot was at a service area at 5AM (was the first batch). The side of blackened ranch was zesty and paired well with the crispy and spicy tenders. Hit the sweet spot for us and left us feeling so satisfied. Would definitely come back here in the future. Very friendly customer service.

reviews.text: The food was beautiful and artfully prepared...delicious and the portion is standard for most Japanese restaurants...the prices were a little on the high side which accounts for the 4 rather than 5 star review

I don't like that two stars says meh, but three says a-ok and i wouldn't go that far. I had heard good things about this place from trustworthy friends, so I wanted to check it out. I went there recently and I have to say I have definitely experience better (which follows the meh in the two star description). I ordered the salmon combo (yes, points off from me for creativity, but the basics provide a good grounds for a sampling. and I was having a craving, so there) and it was very mediocre. The salmon roll was cut haphazardly and the rice was a little too gummy. The sashimi wasn't perfectly cut and was almost chewy and the sushi was diminished by the not quite right rice. The quality of the fish was excellent though, and that was good. I would not object to going back to Hikari if friends wanted to go (and I would of course like to try more of their menu and give them a shot at earning the third star), but given my druthers, I will choose Zento in Old City any day.
This is my go to sushi spot if I'm in the city. Some how I always manage to find parking here. The chirashi is fresh and the BYOB is always a plus ! Def goin here again if I'm in the area !
